# GitHub Personal Access Token
# This token is used to increase API rate limits when fetching repository data
# 
# To create a token:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a descriptive name (e.g., "Portfolio Website")
# 4. Select scopes: public_repo (or repo for private repos)
# 5. Click "Generate token" and copy the token
# 
# For local development:
# 1. Create a .env file in the root directory
# 2. Add the line below with your token:
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# For production builds (GitHub Actions, Vercel, Netlify, etc.):
# Add VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN as an environment variable/secret in your deployment platform
# 
# Note: The token must be prefixed with VITE_ to be available in the browser context

